WEBVTT

00:25.851 --> 00:27.897
[jazz song playing]

01:12.115 --> 01:17.947
And here we havean elegant glass of winefor an elegant beauty.

01:19.775 --> 01:21.733
You're a lot different
than the guys I go
to college with, Martin.

01:21.777 --> 01:23.561
Boys.

01:23.605 --> 01:25.302
The boys at your school.

01:29.176 --> 01:31.787
Don't you get lonely
living out here
all by yourself?

01:33.658 --> 01:37.619
It can be, as I don'tleave often, but, uh...

01:41.013 --> 01:43.538
not when I havegood company, Stacy.

01:44.756 --> 01:46.454
Yeah, it is beautiful.

01:47.977 --> 01:49.979
It is, isn't it?

01:54.201 --> 01:57.029
- It's peaceful.
- [whispers] Yeah.

01:58.205 --> 01:59.336
Private.

02:01.469 --> 02:03.732
It's very private.

02:05.821 --> 02:08.301
It's home.

02:08.345 --> 02:11.696
It's really late.
I should be
getting home, so...

02:11.740 --> 02:15.396
Look, I just want you
to be comfortable here.

02:17.180 --> 02:18.399
With me.

02:20.227 --> 02:22.011
You understand.

02:33.240 --> 02:36.765
Please, just stay
a little bit longer.

02:41.073 --> 02:43.075
Finish your wine, huh?

02:43.119 --> 02:44.990
Don't leave yet.

03:00.615 --> 03:01.920
'Cause you see...

03:03.226 --> 03:06.360
Stacy, I don't want you
to leave.

03:06.403 --> 03:07.709
[music gets distorted]

03:07.752 --> 03:09.754
This is your home now.

03:14.411 --> 03:17.153
What's-- what's happening?

03:26.293 --> 03:28.469
You see, Stacy...

03:28.512 --> 03:32.037
Where I may be different
from all the boys at college,

03:32.081 --> 03:33.996
sadly you are exactly
like all of the other whores

03:34.039 --> 03:36.564
that come here.

03:36.607 --> 03:38.435
[weakly] I just want to go home.

03:43.658 --> 03:45.312
You see, like I told you.

03:45.355 --> 03:47.618
You are home.

03:47.662 --> 03:49.620
♪♪

03:54.930 --> 03:56.148
[thud]

04:03.895 --> 04:05.593
[breathing hard]

04:07.986 --> 04:09.553
[grunting]

04:13.340 --> 04:15.037
[breathing hard]

04:35.971 --> 04:38.278
[eerie sound]

04:49.637 --> 04:51.291
[growling]

04:55.991 --> 04:57.645
[snarling]

05:11.093 --> 05:12.834
[growling]

05:17.447 --> 05:18.883
[screaming]

05:18.927 --> 05:21.103
[ripping sounds]

05:29.807 --> 05:32.810
♪♪

07:13.520 --> 07:16.087
[Thomas] All right, GPS says
it's 10 miles from here.

07:16.131 --> 07:18.133
[Juliet] Yeah, you said that
like half an hour ago, Dad.

07:18.176 --> 07:20.178
[Bernice] Give it a rest,
Juliet.

07:22.920 --> 07:24.487
[Thomas] Watch yourself there.

07:26.794 --> 07:28.926
- You okay?
- [Bernice] I'm gonna get
something to drink.

07:28.970 --> 07:31.451
- You want anything, babe?
- Uh, no, thank you.

07:31.494 --> 07:34.628
I'm gonna call the movers,
see what they're up to.

07:34.671 --> 07:36.891
- I wanna get
something, Mom.
- Okay. Wendy?

07:38.719 --> 07:40.764
You're not coming,
Juliet?

07:40.808 --> 07:43.463
Anything to get out
of the stupid car.

07:48.729 --> 07:50.470
[door bell rings]

07:54.386 --> 07:56.954
- Good afternoon, folks.
- [Bernice] Afternoon!

07:56.998 --> 07:59.522
We're gonna get
some snacks.

07:59.566 --> 08:01.785
[cashier] Not a problem,
ma'am.

08:04.571 --> 08:06.921
So what brings you outto these parts, if youdon't mind me asking?

08:06.964 --> 08:09.532
We, um, don't geta lot of visitors.

08:09.576 --> 08:12.143
Billy Bloomfield!

08:12.187 --> 08:16.583
If you're gonna steal from me,at least make an attemptto be sneaky about it.

08:16.626 --> 08:19.673
I'm guessin' you don't
want me to call
the sheriff, Billy. Mm?

08:24.895 --> 08:26.201
Sorry about that,ma'am.

08:26.244 --> 08:28.072
Boy and his brothersare nothing but trouble,

08:28.116 --> 08:31.641
- have been
since they were little.
- Sorry to hear that.

08:31.685 --> 08:35.645
- Juliet, let's go.
- I'm still looking, Mom.

08:38.082 --> 08:40.302
We're actually moving in
down the road a ways.

08:40.345 --> 08:41.782
Oh, is that so?

08:41.825 --> 08:43.131
I'm guessing that will make you

08:43.174 --> 08:44.785
more than just visitorsaround here, then.

08:44.828 --> 08:46.613
I didn't know there wereany places for sale.

08:46.656 --> 08:48.876
Oh, it's an old farmhouse
with some orchards.

08:48.919 --> 08:50.617
[Bernice]
That's enough, Lisa.

08:50.660 --> 08:52.488
- The old Ellsbury place.
- [Bernice] Yeah, yeah.

08:52.532 --> 08:54.534
I guess that's the one.

08:54.577 --> 08:56.274
[Billy] You're moving
into a serial killer's house,

08:56.318 --> 08:57.798
and you're worried about
your daughter smiling at me?

08:57.841 --> 08:58.973
You shut your mouth,
Billy!

08:59.016 --> 09:00.278
How much do I owe you?

09:00.322 --> 09:01.628
What does he mean, Mom?

09:01.671 --> 09:04.456
Um... No, it'son the house, ma'am.

09:04.500 --> 09:06.546
What do you mean,
it's on the house?

09:06.589 --> 09:08.199
Mom, what
did he mean?

09:08.243 --> 09:10.680
Consider it a welcometo the neighborhood,

09:10.724 --> 09:14.510
and-and an apologyfor the wordsof a moron.

09:14.554 --> 09:16.599
[Bernice] It's really
not necessary.

09:16.643 --> 09:18.645
- Thank you.
- No. My pleasure.

09:20.385 --> 09:22.649
- Welcome to our little town.
- Thanks.

09:26.217 --> 09:28.306
- Let's go, Juliet.
- See you around.

09:28.350 --> 09:31.614
- [door bell rings]
- Miss?

09:31.658 --> 09:34.574
I can assure you he's not
the type of guy you want
to get involved with.

09:34.617 --> 09:37.054
Mm... maybe.

09:37.098 --> 09:40.580
But sometimes people
aren't what they seem
to be on the surface.

09:40.623 --> 09:42.451
Juliet! Now!

09:43.800 --> 09:45.846
Okay, Mom.

09:51.634 --> 09:52.853
[door closes]

09:59.424 --> 10:00.817
[door bell rings]

10:10.653 --> 10:12.786
Yeah, Mindy,
it's, uh, Henry here.

10:14.091 --> 10:16.746
I need to talk
to the sheriff.

10:16.790 --> 10:19.444
♪♪

10:19.488 --> 10:21.664
[Juliet] You guys have
to stop treating me
like I'm a child.

10:21.708 --> 10:24.536
When am I gonna get
a say on what's good
for me?

10:24.580 --> 10:27.104
It's bad enough we're movinginto some serial killer's house.

10:27.148 --> 10:28.279
[brakes screech]

10:29.672 --> 10:31.108
Thomas?

10:33.328 --> 10:35.025
Just breathe,honey.

10:35.069 --> 10:36.636
Dad, I didn't--
I didn't mean to--

10:36.679 --> 10:39.987
Juliet, please!Stop talking!

10:43.991 --> 10:45.209
You did good.

10:45.253 --> 10:49.300
This place is...it's great.

10:49.344 --> 10:52.347
It's exactlywhat we need as a fa--

10:52.390 --> 10:53.653
[Bernice gasps]

10:57.526 --> 10:58.788
I'm okay.

11:01.138 --> 11:02.662
Yes.

11:02.705 --> 11:05.316
Yes, you are.

11:05.360 --> 11:06.883
We all are.

11:08.755 --> 11:10.147
We're gonna be okay.

11:15.762 --> 11:18.155
Juliet, hey.

11:18.199 --> 11:20.767
Look, I know you're not
happy about the move,
but you have to trust me.

11:20.810 --> 11:22.638
This is what's best
for our family.

11:33.823 --> 11:36.130
[Thomas] Look at this.

11:36.173 --> 11:38.741
Past these trees up here,
you can see the orchard.

11:38.785 --> 11:41.309
♪♪

11:52.146 --> 11:55.976
[Bernice] And here...
is our beautiful, new home.

12:09.554 --> 12:11.339
This one's
a little heavy.

12:11.382 --> 12:12.819
All right.

12:19.739 --> 12:22.393
You're the best.
You're just the best.

12:25.440 --> 12:27.224
- [Bernice] Hey.
- [chuckling] Hey!

12:27.268 --> 12:29.270
- Here you go.
- Is anything in there?

12:29.313 --> 12:32.490
Yes! A surprise.

12:32.534 --> 12:34.231
- [ice rattles]
- [lid closes]

12:34.275 --> 12:37.017
- Thank you.
Appreciate it.
- Of course.

12:39.933 --> 12:41.586
- [Bernice] She'll be okay.
- You think so?

12:41.630 --> 12:45.677
Mm-hmm. We were just like her
when we were that age.

12:47.549 --> 12:49.029
It was a differenttime then.

12:49.072 --> 12:51.335
We lived in a big city,

12:51.379 --> 12:53.033
you could still feel safein that big city.

12:53.076 --> 12:56.514
Now, no matterwhere you go...I don't know.

12:56.558 --> 12:59.213
I just-- I don'twant them exposed.

12:59.256 --> 13:03.043
Even small towns
are dangerous, Thomas.

13:03.086 --> 13:06.046
How did Julietfind out?

13:06.089 --> 13:09.266
The clerk and some punk
in the store.

13:09.310 --> 13:11.399
- Yeah? Hey.
- Yeah.

13:11.442 --> 13:14.054
- Yes? Okay.
- Yes.

13:14.097 --> 13:16.926
- How much
do the girls know?
- Enough.

13:20.060 --> 13:24.151
Times change,
and we have to do
what we have to do,

13:24.194 --> 13:28.677
and we're raising them right,
and that is all that matters.

13:35.466 --> 13:38.513
Take it to the girls
up there or I'll keep
kissing you.

13:38.556 --> 13:39.949
[Bernice] Girls! Why
don't you guys take a break

13:39.993 --> 13:41.168
and come get some water?

13:42.256 --> 13:44.432
- You spoil them!
- Hmm.

13:44.475 --> 13:46.173
There she is!

13:48.566 --> 13:50.264
Dad, remind me why
the movers

13:50.307 --> 13:52.875
didn't actually move anything
inside the house?

13:52.919 --> 13:56.270
Well, they did, first of all,
but we moved here
for privacy.

13:56.313 --> 13:58.620
You don't want a bunch
of strangers going in
and out of your house,

13:58.663 --> 14:00.100
carrying your stuff.
You don't want that.

14:00.143 --> 14:01.841
- I don't care.
- Well, you should care

14:01.884 --> 14:04.234
and should start learninga little more responsibility.

14:04.278 --> 14:06.715
You got the most boxes.

14:06.758 --> 14:08.543
Can we eat the fruitfrom the orchard, Dad?

14:08.586 --> 14:09.892
Uh, no.

14:09.936 --> 14:11.851
Yeah, but not now,
it's not the season.

14:11.894 --> 14:14.288
But when it is
in season, yes.

14:14.331 --> 14:16.507
If we're here
for that long.

14:16.551 --> 14:18.031
Hey!

14:19.684 --> 14:23.384
- Sorry.
- Are you?

14:23.427 --> 14:26.300
- Yeah, Dad.
- I'm sorry, actually.

14:26.343 --> 14:28.868
Okay? I'm sorry.

14:30.565 --> 14:32.697
I know it's been really hard
for you guys this move.

14:32.741 --> 14:35.875
It's crazy. It's been
a lot of sacrifices.

14:35.918 --> 14:40.096
But look, we-we can't argue,we can-- we can getthrough this like a family.

14:40.140 --> 14:41.706
This is a good thing,okay?

14:43.099 --> 14:45.014
I just want you safe.

14:47.756 --> 14:49.279
I want you safe.

14:49.323 --> 14:51.716
♪♪

14:51.760 --> 14:53.414
I thought you said
you could play, kid.

14:55.416 --> 14:57.461
- Don't call me kid.
- Ha!

14:57.505 --> 15:00.334
Whatever you say.

15:03.076 --> 15:06.122
- Where have you been?
- On the road.

15:07.776 --> 15:10.866
Some of us have actually
have to work for a living.

15:10.910 --> 15:13.825
- Yeah.
- Guess you're about
to find out...

15:16.611 --> 15:19.135
when I take the rest
of your money, Billy.

15:22.051 --> 15:23.835
- I got a job.
- That so?

15:23.879 --> 15:25.663
Mm-hmm.

15:25.707 --> 15:30.407
Billy, I've known you
since you were
in grade school,

15:30.451 --> 15:33.323
and you ain't never
had a job.

15:33.367 --> 15:37.110
Not unless you call catching
the scraps from your big
brothers a profession.

15:38.807 --> 15:40.156
Well, what can I say?

15:41.723 --> 15:44.030
Some of us are
just late bloomers, I guess.

15:44.073 --> 15:49.600
Well, one thing for sure is,
you ain't making no money
playing pool, kid.

15:52.473 --> 15:53.909
What the fuck?!

15:53.953 --> 15:56.129
I told you
not to call me kid.

15:58.261 --> 16:01.134
- Nice job, Bill.
Thanks.
- Lenny. Daryl.

16:02.613 --> 16:04.354
What the fuck is going on?

16:04.398 --> 16:06.313
What's going on is,you owe us money,and for whatever reason

16:06.356 --> 16:08.489
you're dumb enoughto come around herewithout paying us.

16:08.532 --> 16:10.273
I've got
your fucking money, Lenny!

16:10.317 --> 16:11.796
You've gotmy fucking money, huh?

16:11.840 --> 16:13.885
You mean that moneyright there?

16:13.929 --> 16:16.062
That money lookslike Billy's money,doesn't it?

16:20.588 --> 16:22.242
It's in my back pocket.

16:23.417 --> 16:24.635
Okay.

16:25.723 --> 16:27.943
Hey, hey, hey!Calm down, Vinny.

16:27.987 --> 16:29.901
Calm down. Hey,we're good?

16:33.253 --> 16:34.602
- [sighs] Oh, Vinny, Vinny!
- Lenny.

16:34.645 --> 16:36.386
- What am I going to do?
What?
- Lenny...

16:36.430 --> 16:38.954
You think the glassyou smoke is free?

16:41.696 --> 16:43.306
Yeah, I didn't think so.

16:43.350 --> 16:45.265
Lenny, seriously...

16:45.308 --> 16:46.918
- I can tell
all the time...
- I can get the money.

16:46.962 --> 16:48.833
I need the money.Hang on one second,all right?

16:48.877 --> 16:50.618
[Vinny gasps]

16:54.143 --> 16:56.972
[grunts]

16:57.016 --> 16:59.235
- [Lenny sighs]
- [grunting continues]

16:59.279 --> 17:02.456
- Good job, Bill.
- It's nothing.

17:12.074 --> 17:14.685
[Billy] I may have
something bigger for us.

17:14.729 --> 17:16.557
Gotta scope the place
out a little bit,

17:16.599 --> 17:20.300
but we should be able
to check it out
tomorrow night.

17:21.997 --> 17:24.260
- Tomorrow night?
- Hmm.

17:24.304 --> 17:26.435
If you say so.

17:33.139 --> 17:34.575
[Billy sniffs]

17:48.023 --> 17:49.764
How is it looking?

17:49.807 --> 17:53.115
Well, we're looking
like the previous owner
didn't have cable.

17:53.159 --> 17:56.466
We're looking likethis house is old,Mr. Delaney.

17:56.510 --> 17:58.990
But most of the placesout here are,

17:59.034 --> 18:01.602
so I'm sure
it won't be a problem.

18:01.645 --> 18:04.039
- It'll be fine,
Bernice.
- We have to leave soon.

18:04.083 --> 18:06.911
Don't worry about that.
I'll take care of this,
it's okay.

18:06.955 --> 18:08.261
Everything's okay.

18:08.304 --> 18:10.872
[Juliet chuckles]Well, that's debatable.

18:10.915 --> 18:13.004
Hey, we're about
to have cable TV.

18:13.048 --> 18:15.442
Dad, I-I don't wanna
stay here with them.

18:15.485 --> 18:17.618
I-I wanna go
with you guys.

18:20.360 --> 18:22.449
[Bernice] We've beenthrough this already.

18:22.492 --> 18:25.016
I just don't understand
why you guys can't treat me
like an adult.

18:25.060 --> 18:27.454
We're having you watch
your sisters. That is
treating you like an adult.

18:27.497 --> 18:29.456
- Are we having steak
for dinner?
- Of course.

18:29.499 --> 18:31.371
- It's already been ordered.
- Dad, that is not
what I mean.

18:31.414 --> 18:34.678
I know what you mean.
Just stop treating us
like it's a punishment.

18:34.722 --> 18:37.464
- You're just helping out.
- I am going crazy
already, though.

18:37.507 --> 18:41.163
I know, sweetheart.But I need you to stay here.

18:41.207 --> 18:43.600
[groans] Cable
is almost set,
Ms. Delaney.

18:43.644 --> 18:45.776
- Oh, wow! Great.
- Oh!

18:45.820 --> 18:49.519
Well, I'm sure there's
something I can find
to do here.

18:50.825 --> 18:51.956
Excuse me.

18:52.000 --> 18:53.741
Okay, we're all donehere, my man.

18:53.784 --> 18:55.656
Okay? I need yououtside, though.

18:55.699 --> 18:56.744
Juliet...

18:57.875 --> 18:59.790
Hey, buddy.
Let's go.

18:59.834 --> 19:02.228
You need
to control yourself.

19:04.752 --> 19:07.581
The body of a single mother
of two was found
late last night

19:07.624 --> 19:09.539
just a few feet from where
I am currently standing,

19:09.583 --> 19:11.846
bringing the current
body total to seven,

19:11.889 --> 19:13.935
from the latest
freeway killer.

19:13.978 --> 19:16.155
All victims have been
female, strangled,

19:16.198 --> 19:18.374
and picked up along
the historic route 66,

19:18.418 --> 19:20.159
and dumped in various locations,

19:20.202 --> 19:23.423
the latest of which,
this abandoned building
seen behind me.

19:23.466 --> 19:27.383
Local state police
are advising anyone
traveling along route 66

19:27.427 --> 19:29.994
to not travel alone.
They're also asking
no hitchhiking

19:30.038 --> 19:33.172
in the wake of the ongoing
search for this killer.

19:33.215 --> 19:36.044
- Those poor women!
- And that's that.

19:36.087 --> 19:38.742
- Dad! I was watching that!
- And now you're not.

19:38.786 --> 19:41.005
You know you can't shield mefrom everything forever, right?

19:41.049 --> 19:42.485
She's right about that,
honey.

19:42.529 --> 19:44.618
Yeah, she's right
about the "forever" part.

19:46.881 --> 19:49.188
I just--
let's cancel the trip.

19:49.231 --> 19:51.973
- Cancel it.
- We can't cancel the trip.

19:52.016 --> 19:54.758
We can't cancel the trip
even if you wanted
to cancel the trip.

19:54.802 --> 19:57.935
Or you could bring me
with you on the trip.

20:00.938 --> 20:03.332
Fine! I will be
in my room.

20:04.638 --> 20:07.249
It's two days.

20:07.293 --> 20:09.338
Love you,
sweetie.

20:10.644 --> 20:12.167
I'm not hungry now.

20:15.301 --> 20:18.042
♪♪

20:27.182 --> 20:30.098
- [radio crackles]
- Mindy, come in.

20:30.141 --> 20:32.535
Go ahead, Sheriff.

20:32.579 --> 20:34.058
Any luck locating
them boys?

20:35.756 --> 20:38.062
No, Sheriff. All the usual
places were checked.

20:38.106 --> 20:39.281
No sign of them.

20:39.325 --> 20:41.849
♪♪

20:45.113 --> 20:46.332
[lighter flicks]

20:50.727 --> 20:53.339
- See what I mean?
- What makes you think
they have money?

20:53.382 --> 20:56.385
Nice car,
from the city.

21:01.085 --> 21:02.522
Do you have to do
that here?

21:05.176 --> 21:07.091
How many are there?

21:07.135 --> 21:09.006
Mom, Dad, couple girls.

21:09.050 --> 21:11.052
Two or three, I can't
really remember.

21:12.532 --> 21:15.099
Don't strain yourself, Bill.

21:20.801 --> 21:22.803
[both laughing]

21:25.153 --> 21:28.069
- You guys leaving?
- Yes.

21:28.112 --> 21:30.376
- You girls be good
for your sister.
- We will, I promise.

21:30.419 --> 21:32.987
Hey, I left some money
on the counter in case
you need anything.

21:33.030 --> 21:35.729
- Okay? I love you, girls.
- We love you too, Dad.

21:35.772 --> 21:37.861
I know it. You better.

21:37.905 --> 21:40.081
I love you.
Give Mom some love, okay?

21:40.124 --> 21:42.692
Get in here. Oh!
I love you, girls.

21:42.736 --> 21:44.781
Me too.Have a good trip.

21:44.825 --> 21:47.088
Thank you.
You girls be safe.

21:47.131 --> 21:50.221
- All right.
- Oh, God!

21:50.265 --> 21:52.398
You know your daughter
is up to something, right?

21:52.441 --> 21:55.096
Oh, yeah, I do.
She's our daughter.

21:55.139 --> 21:57.403
But she usually is,
so yes, I do.

21:57.446 --> 21:59.840
- You know what I mean.
- I do.

21:59.883 --> 22:02.059
I know what you mean.
We've been over this,
remember?

22:02.103 --> 22:06.237
I'm just worried maybeshe won't be able to handlewhatever she gets herself into.

22:06.281 --> 22:10.503
Juliet? Come on.
She's our daughter.

22:10.546 --> 22:13.157
She's your girl too.
She can handle anything.

22:13.201 --> 22:15.029
- Okay.
- Not gonna be able
to get-- Juliet?

